data-triple-N3.o: "The Irish Republic (Irish: Poblacht na hEireann or Saorstat Eireann) was a revolutionary state that declared its independence from Great Britain in January 1919. It established a legislature, a government, a court system and a police force. At the same time, the Irish Volunteers, who came under the control of the Dail and became known as the Irish Republican Army, fought against British armed forces in the Irish War of Independence."@en
